    "interpretation": "Graph-based detection (Louvain on funding-flow proxy) provides substantially stronger detection of real sybils than rule-based or feature-based detectors. However, LLM-generated sybils, which are designed with low RF and MA values, effectively evade graph-based detection by avoiding the funding clusters that Louvain identifies. This demonstrates that LLM sybils present a fundamental challenge across ALL detector modalities: rules, statistical, and structural.",
